67
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:17,666
Chi!

68
00:07:22,666 --> 00:07:23,866
Hideki?

69
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:37,033
What is it? Is there
something the matter?

70
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,766
Actually, that's
what I'd like to know.

71
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,966
Oh, that was scary!

72
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:42,333
What was scary?

73
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,133
Chi has been located!

74
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,866
I repeat: Chi has been located!

75
00:07:51,933 --> 00:07:53,300
Sumomo.

76
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:19,000
Chi.

77
00:08:22,433 --> 00:08:24,466
Alright, I've gotta find
some way to get her home.

78
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,966
1, 2, 3.

79
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,966
I guess that's it then.

80
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,500
There's no other way.

81
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:35,266
Hey mister, is that a Persocom?

82
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,500
Yeah.

83
00:08:36,566 --> 00:08:38,533
Looks like it froze
while you guys were out.

84
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,633
I suppose Persocoms
are rather useful,

85
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:43,033
but it looks like it cost you
this time, didn't it, Buddy?

86
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:46,233
I guess. Yeah

87
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:51,333
But, Chi is a very
valuable Persocom for me.

88
00:08:55,466 --> 00:08:57,133
And so...

89
00:09:16,366 --> 00:09:17,366
I don't know how, 

90
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:19,533
but that didn't
feel like a dream.

91
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,033
It felt like I was in
some kind of action movie.

92
00:09:25,466 --> 00:09:28,066
That whole thing is
one big mystery to me.

93
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:29,766
And it all really happened, too.

94
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:32,600
Yet here she is,
sleeping so peacefully.

95
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:34,200
But, wait...

96
00:09:34,266 --> 00:09:36,600
She looks like she's sleeping,

97
00:09:36,666 --> 00:09:40,500
but that's not
really sleeping. Is it?

98
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:45,866
Come to think of it, she
hasn't moved a bit all night.

99
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:49,866
It's not like she'll
never move again, right?

100
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,366
Chi.

101
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:53,733
What would happen
if she never moved again?

102
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,566
Chi! Wake up, okay? Chi!

103
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:01,033
What if... she stayed
like this forever?

104
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,066
Chi! What's wrong with you, Chi?

105
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:05,733
Wake up!

106
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,300
Chi.

107
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,166
Hideki.

108
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:12,500
Chi!

109
00:10:12,566 --> 00:10:15,033
Hideki! Hideki! Hideki!

110
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,033
Hey!

111
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,566
Chi.

112
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:22,666
Chi.

113
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,233
I'm glad, Chi.

114
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,833
Lord Minoru,

115
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:42,766
Would you like some more tea?

116
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:45,566
Thanks, I could
certainly use some.

117
00:10:49,366 --> 00:10:52,800
Miss Chi, I wonder
if she is alright now.

118
00:10:52,866 --> 00:10:55,466
Mr. Shinbo sent me an
e-mail a little while ago.

119
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,866
They managed to
find her somehow,

120
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:00,333
and were able to bring her home.

121
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,733
Oh how fortunate.

122
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,900
I'm so glad it all worked out.

123
00:11:03,966 --> 00:11:05,700
What I don't understand...

124
00:11:05,766 --> 00:11:07,933
is what could make
every computer

125
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,900
in the area freeze up like
that all of a sudden.

126
00:11:10,966 --> 00:11:12,466
And, you don't
seem to understand

127
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:14,333
why it happened either.

128
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,300
Isn't that right, Yuzuki?

129
00:11:16,366 --> 00:11:19,300
I do not.

130
00:11:19,366 --> 00:11:20,366
However...

131
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:21,733
However?

132
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,233
Surely...

133
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,633
I think...

134
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:27,866
Yes, I'm sure I heard some
kind of voice in my head.

135
00:11:27,933 --> 00:11:28,900
Who was it?

136
00:11:28,966 --> 00:11:30,466
I don't know.

137
00:11:32,966 --> 00:11:34,933
Although...

138
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:49,200
That's right...

139
00:11:49,266 --> 00:11:51,466
It seems to me that
it was very familiar,

140
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:53,966
as if the voice
of someone I know.

141
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:55,600
It seemed.

142
00:11:56,266 --> 00:11:57,400
It was a job.

143
00:11:57,466 --> 00:12:00,866
Oh yeah? I don't suppose
you'd care to repeat that?

144
00:12:00,933 --> 00:12:03,666
Chi got a job yesterday.

145
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:06,133
I told you no, what's so
difficult to understand?

146
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,633
I said no working at
anything shady like that!

147
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:12,600
Hideki said no,
don't do a shady job.

148
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:15,000
So, Chi didn't do a shady job.

149
00:12:15,066 --> 00:12:16,300
Well as far as jobs go,

150
00:12:16,366 --> 00:12:18,233
I'd have to say a peep
show is pretty shady.

151
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,566
Chi?

152
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:20,800
But the man told Chi,

153
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:23,633
"Oh yeah, it's a
really good job."

154
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:27,366
Oh! Those kinda guys'll
always say things like that!

155
00:12:27,433 --> 00:12:31,033
He said Hideki would be
happy if Chi finds good job.

156
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,066
Huh?

157
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:33,233
And Hideki said that he wanted

158
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,933
to buy lots of
things with money.

159
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:39,600
Yeah, you're right. I did.

160
00:12:39,666 --> 00:12:41,733
I guess I must've
said some stupid things

161
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,266
that made you do that.

162
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:45,133
Ah...

163
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,900
Huh?

164
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:48,800
Did Chi make mistake?

165
00:12:48,866 --> 00:12:49,766
Um.

166
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,400
Is Chi bad?

167
00:12:51,466 --> 00:12:53,800
Well, no. Not bad.

168
00:12:53,866 --> 00:12:55,200
Chi isn't bad or anything.

169
00:12:55,266 --> 00:12:58,200
I didn't mean...
You're not bad at all.

170
00:12:58,266 --> 00:12:59,933
Is that true?

171
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,933
Yeah!

172
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,700
Oh, Chi.

173
00:13:05,866 --> 00:13:07,900
Don't think that, Chi.
You're not bad!

174
00:13:10,566 --> 00:13:14,200
Chi does not want
Hideki to hate Chi.

175
00:13:14,266 --> 00:13:16,066
Because Hideki is Chi's-

176
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:18,566
I really appreciate
what you're saying, but...

177
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:20,733
Um... look, Chi, I don't
want you to think you have

178
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,566
to go out of your way
to work or anything.

179
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:23,566
But why?

180
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:26,100
Hideki told Chi that
would make him happy.

181
00:13:26,166 --> 00:13:27,400
Mmm...

182
00:13:27,466 --> 00:13:28,966
Okay, what do you
think about this?

183
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:31,800
If you really want to get a job,
I'll go help you find one.

184
00:13:31,866 --> 00:13:33,200
But until I find you something,

185
00:13:33,266 --> 00:13:37,466
you'll have to stay
at home. How 'bout that?

186
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:39,733
Thank you, Hideki.

187
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,666
Chi's happy now.

188
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,833
No, not you.

189
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:49,566
After all, I'm the one
who should be saying thanks.

190
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,300
I really mean it.
Thank you, Chi.

191
00:13:51,366 --> 00:13:53,466
'Cause you did it all for me.

192
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:54,833
Chi.

193
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,333
You need to be careful here,

194
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,800
due to the fact that this
particular phrase uses "tamae."

195
00:13:58,866 --> 00:13:59,766
A part-time job...

196
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:02,766
one that isn't shady
or even questionable,

197
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:04,666
But that'll still
consider hiring Chi,

198
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:07,766
even though she's a little short
in the common sense department.

199
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,966
Hmm...

200
